WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.045 --> 00:00:04.787
♪ O holy night

2
00:00:04.830 --> 00:00:09.009
♪ The stars are
brightly shining... ♪

3
00:00:09.052 --> 00:00:12.055
Hi. sorry to bother you. Lance.
It's just. um. uh...

4
00:00:12.099 --> 00:00:14.101
Dasha. she hasn't come down
to the car yet.

5
00:00:14.144 --> 00:00:16.190
And that's my problem
because...?

6
00:00:16.233 --> 00:00:18.670
Well. we'll be late
to the match?

7
00:00:18.714 --> 00:00:20.281
Clara. this is your job.

8
00:00:20.324 --> 00:00:22.892
Or can you not handle the simple
act of picking up a client?

9
00:00:22.935 --> 00:00:24.894
I-I called her.
I pounded on the door.

10
00:00:24.937 --> 00:00:26.809
She's-she's not answering.

11
00:00:26.852 --> 00:00:28.506
Then use your Ivy League brain

12
00:00:28.550 --> 00:00:30.943
and figure out how to get
inside her room and wake her up.

13
00:00:31.770 --> 00:00:32.945
You mean. break in?

14
00:00:32.989 --> 00:00:34.208
I don't care how you do it.

15
00:00:34.251 --> 00:00:35.426
Bribe the front desk
for a room key.

16
00:00:35.470 --> 00:00:36.688
Charm a bellboy.

17
00:00:36.732 --> 00:00:38.342
Do whatever it takes
or you're fired.

18
00:00:38.386 --> 00:00:40.344
:
Merry Christmas!

19
00:00:40.388 --> 00:00:41.737
Whoa. Sorry.

20
00:00:41.780 --> 00:00:43.130
It's okay. No problem.

21
00:00:44.783 --> 00:00:46.002
Dasha? Are you up?

22
00:00:46.046 --> 00:00:47.743
Hey. Jade.

23
00:00:47.786 --> 00:00:49.049
Have you seen Dasha?

24
00:00:49.092 --> 00:00:50.093
She's not answering her phone.

25
00:00:50.137 --> 00:00:51.573
Not since last night. Sorry.

26
00:00:51.616 --> 00:00:53.096
Yeah. She probably overslept.

27
00:00:53.140 --> 00:00:54.097
I've got to run.

28
00:00:54.141 --> 00:00:55.403
First match back
since my surgery.

29
00:00:55.446 --> 00:00:57.231
Hope my hip holds up
for a three-setter.

30
00:00:57.274 --> 00:00:59.233
Yep. Good luck out there.

31
00:00:59.276 --> 00:01:02.018
♪ O night

32
00:01:02.062 --> 00:01:04.368
♪ Divine

33
00:01:04.412 --> 00:01:05.891
Dasha?

34
00:01:08.633 --> 00:01:10.244
Dasha. it's morning.

35
00:01:10.287 --> 00:01:12.159
Let's get moving.

36
00:01:12.202 --> 00:01:14.509
If you shower fast.
we can still make it on time.

37
00:01:15.336 --> 00:01:17.512
Come on. Dasha.
It's an important tournament.

38
00:01:17.555 --> 00:01:19.253
Dasha. wake up.

39
00:01:22.169 --> 00:01:24.388
Dasha?

40
00:01:24.432 --> 00:01:26.390
Oh. my God. Please. no.

41
00:01:26.434 --> 00:01:28.349
Please. please. please. no.

42
00:01:29.872 --> 00:01:32.396
Help. I need help.
She's not breathing!

43
00:01:32.440 --> 00:01:35.138
♪ The angel voices...

44
00:01:35.182 --> 00:01:36.618
Thank you. Pastor.

45
00:01:36.661 --> 00:01:39.142
Mr. Palmer. a word?

46
00:01:39.186 --> 00:01:40.361
Uh-oh.

47
00:01:40.404 --> 00:01:42.493
Never good when the pastor
calls you Mister

48
00:01:42.537 --> 00:01:44.016
and says they need a word.

49
00:01:44.060 --> 00:01:47.194
There's a congregant.
Clara Williams.

50
00:01:47.237 --> 00:01:48.586
a good girl.

51
00:01:48.630 --> 00:01:50.806
Works the soup kitchen
every Saturday.

52
00:01:50.849 --> 00:01:52.416
rain or shine.
Mm-hmm.

53
00:01:52.460 --> 00:01:53.809
She's in trouble.

54
00:01:53.852 --> 00:01:55.463
Okay. What kind of trouble?

55
00:01:55.506 --> 00:01:58.814
Did you hear about
Dasha Markovic's overdose?

56
00:01:58.857 --> 00:02:00.946
Oh. yeah. yeah. It was tragic.

57
00:02:00.990 --> 00:02:03.253
Clara is being charged
with her death.

58
00:02:03.297 --> 00:02:06.300
She gave her the drugs
that killed her.

59
00:02:06.343 --> 00:02:08.215
So... big trouble.

60
00:02:08.258 --> 00:02:11.174
She needs a lawyer.
Can you help her?

61
00:02:11.218 --> 00:02:13.307
Pastor. I would.
I would love to.

62
00:02:13.350 --> 00:02:15.004
but TAC's shutting down
for the holidays. and...

63
00:02:15.047 --> 00:02:17.920
It'd be a true gesture
of Christian goodwill.

64
00:02:17.963 --> 00:02:19.313
A way to give back

65
00:02:19.356 --> 00:02:20.444
this season of giving.

66
00:02:20.488 --> 00:02:22.838
I hear you. Pastor. but...

67
00:02:22.881 --> 00:02:26.015
TAC charges
some pretty hefty fees.

68
00:02:26.798 --> 00:02:28.844
We have money.

69
00:02:29.845 --> 00:02:31.847
You got any more excuses?

70
00:02:31.890 --> 00:02:33.718
♪

71
00:02:36.939 --> 00:02:39.159
You got guilt-tripped
by your pastor.

72
00:02:39.202 --> 00:02:41.161
It's like every sin
I ever committed

73
00:02:41.204 --> 00:02:43.032
was tattooed to my forehead.

74
00:02:43.075 --> 00:02:45.208
Well. I respect
the church's passion.

75
00:02:45.252 --> 00:02:47.384
but this is about
a quarter of our fee.

76
00:02:47.428 --> 00:02:50.387
Do you want to argue dollars
and cents with Pastor Reynolds?

77
00:02:50.431 --> 00:02:53.738
No. That's why
I don't go to church.

78
00:02:54.783 --> 00:02:58.178
I spent so much time with Dasha
over the last two years.

79
00:02:59.309 --> 00:03:02.094
I know she was a client. but...

80
00:03:02.138 --> 00:03:03.879
it kind of felt
like we were friends.

81
00:03:03.922 --> 00:03:05.837
And the fact
that I gave her something

82
00:03:05.881 --> 00:03:08.231
that killed her...

83
00:03:08.275 --> 00:03:10.320
I don't know
how I'm gonna live with that.

84
00:03:11.147 --> 00:03:12.888
The police report said
that the cocaine

85
00:03:12.931 --> 00:03:14.759
that you gave Dasha
was laced with fentanyl.

86
00:03:14.803 --> 00:03:16.152
It's a powerful opiate.

87
00:03:16.196 --> 00:03:17.545
Look. I know that I never
should have gotten

88
00:03:17.588 --> 00:03:19.068
the cocaine for Dasha
in the first place.

89
00:03:19.111 --> 00:03:20.330
but I never would've given it
to her

90
00:03:20.374 --> 00:03:21.984
if I knew that there was
fentanyl in it.

91
00:03:22.027 --> 00:03:23.464
Well. unfortunately
the prosecutor

92
00:03:23.507 --> 00:03:25.074
doesn't care what you knew.

93
00:03:25.117 --> 00:03:27.903
Tons of street drugs are getting
cut with fentanyl every day.

94
00:03:27.946 --> 00:03:30.384
It's leading to
a massive amount of ODs.

95
00:03:30.427 --> 00:03:32.429
So the D.A.'s office is
taking a hardline

96
00:03:32.473 --> 00:03:35.389
on anyone who is involved
in distributing these drugs.

97
00:03:35.432 --> 00:03:38.087
I don't sell drugs.

98
00:03:38.130 --> 00:03:40.045
I don't even do drugs.
Right.

99
00:03:40.089 --> 00:03:41.177
Why don't we start
at the beginning.

100
00:03:41.221 --> 00:03:42.439
Tell us what happened.

101
00:03:43.440 --> 00:03:45.616
Dasha's agent is my boss.

102
00:03:45.660 --> 00:03:48.576
And as his assistant.
it is my job to service her.

103
00:03:48.619 --> 00:03:49.881
I schedule her meetings.

104
00:03:49.925 --> 00:03:51.666
I make sure that she gets
there on time.

105
00:03:51.709 --> 00:03:54.756
Basically. anything that she
needs. I make sure that she has.

106
00:03:54.799 --> 00:03:56.236
Even when it's cocaine?

107
00:03:57.672 --> 00:03:59.369
My boss made it very clear that

108
00:03:59.413 --> 00:04:02.459
if I didn't give Dasha exactly
what she wanted. he'd fire me.

109
00:04:02.503 --> 00:04:05.723
So. your boss knew that Dasha
had asked you for drugs?

110
00:04:05.767 --> 00:04:07.116
He told me which dealer
to go to.

111
00:04:07.159 --> 00:04:10.206
Told you verbally.
no paper trail?

112
00:04:10.250 --> 00:04:12.426
Lance Thomas's motto is.
"Don't write anything down

113
00:04:12.469 --> 00:04:13.992
unless you want to see it
on social."

114
00:04:14.036 --> 00:04:16.647
Wait. Your boss is
Lance Thomas?

115
00:04:16.691 --> 00:04:18.083
Yes.

116
00:04:20.651 --> 00:04:22.218
Okay. So. your boss is a jerk.

117
00:04:22.262 --> 00:04:23.785
He threatens to fire you
unless you break the law.

118
00:04:23.828 --> 00:04:25.090
Why don't you quit?

119
00:04:25.134 --> 00:04:27.092
Look. I know
it sounds ridiculous.

120
00:04:27.136 --> 00:04:29.181
It is ridiculous.
I just...

121
00:04:30.008 --> 00:04:33.229
Being an athlete has been
my entire life.

122
00:04:33.273 --> 00:04:35.144
I ran track growing up.
and my family.

123
00:04:35.187 --> 00:04:37.451
we didn't have any money.
but because I was fast.

124
00:04:37.494 --> 00:04:38.974
I got to go to college.

125
00:04:39.017 --> 00:04:41.150
I was training for the Olympics
my junior year.

126
00:04:41.193 --> 00:04:42.934
and I got a stress fracture
in my foot.

127
00:04:42.978 --> 00:04:44.675
I did everything
that the doctor said.

128
00:04:44.719 --> 00:04:45.937
but it didn't heal.

129
00:04:45.981 --> 00:04:48.636
So... that was it.

130
00:04:48.679 --> 00:04:50.115
My running career was over.

131
00:04:50.159 --> 00:04:52.335
And so. being an agent was
the next best thing?

132
00:04:52.379 --> 00:04:54.119
It's better in a lot of ways.
actually.

133
00:04:54.163 --> 00:04:55.730
A lot of athletes grow up poor.

134
00:04:55.773 --> 00:04:56.992
like I did.

135
00:04:57.035 --> 00:04:58.646
and they get taken advantage of.

136
00:04:58.689 --> 00:05:00.822
So. I thought...

137
00:05:00.865 --> 00:05:03.868
if I could make it as an agent.
that I could advocate for them.

138
00:05:03.912 --> 00:05:06.001
But first you had to
survive Lance Thomas.

139
00:05:06.044 --> 00:05:07.698
I've had tough coaches
my whole life.

140
00:05:07.742 --> 00:05:10.701
and some of them have been
downright bullies.

141
00:05:10.745 --> 00:05:13.138
But I never let them break me.

142
00:05:13.182 --> 00:05:16.185
And I wasn't about to let Lance
break me.

143
00:05:16.228 --> 00:05:17.447
That's why I stayed.

144
00:05:17.491 --> 00:05:20.102
That's why I did
whatever he told me to do.

145
00:05:20.145 --> 00:05:21.843
I thought I was being strong.

146
00:05:21.886 --> 00:05:23.323
But now I just wish

147
00:05:23.366 --> 00:05:26.108
that I had been strong enough
to walk away.

148
00:05:26.151 --> 00:05:28.937
Then maybe Dasha would
still be alive.

149
00:05:29.720 --> 00:05:32.288
She's guilty.

150
00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:34.377
Never a great way
to start a defense.

151
00:05:34.421 --> 00:05:36.118
I know.

152
00:05:36.161 --> 00:05:38.163
But I feel for Clara.

153
00:05:38.207 --> 00:05:39.556
She just got caught up
in the machine. Bull.

154
00:05:39.600 --> 00:05:42.516
Is that an affirmative defense
I'm not aware of?

155
00:05:42.559 --> 00:05:45.606
No. I'm just saying.
she's young.

156
00:05:45.649 --> 00:05:49.174
She's working in
a high-pressure environment.

157
00:05:49.218 --> 00:05:50.698
It's easy to lose perspective.

158
00:05:50.741 --> 00:05:52.613
Hell. it was like that for me.
When I got to New York

159
00:05:52.656 --> 00:05:55.529
and started working at Vogue.
it was the exact same thing.

160
00:05:55.572 --> 00:05:57.269
Fashion. sports...

161
00:05:57.313 --> 00:05:59.402
Lot of people dream of working
in those industries.

162
00:05:59.446 --> 00:06:00.708
Exactly.

163
00:06:00.751 --> 00:06:02.710
You put up with a lot
just to keep your job.

164
00:06:02.753 --> 00:06:05.800
It starts out. you're picking
your boss's kid up from school.

165
00:06:05.843 --> 00:06:08.455
and then you're picking
your boss's dog's poop up.

166
00:06:08.498 --> 00:06:10.631
So. by the time they tell you
to go buy drugs.

167
00:06:10.674 --> 00:06:12.720
you're programmed just to do it.

168
00:06:12.763 --> 00:06:14.896
You're like a frog
in a boiling pot of water.

169
00:06:14.939 --> 00:06:17.986
You don't realize that you're
in trouble until it's too late.

170
00:06:18.029 --> 00:06:19.553
Well...

171
00:06:19.596 --> 00:06:23.470
Lance Thomas got Clara
in a world of trouble.

172
00:06:24.340 --> 00:06:26.647
What if we try
to shift the blame

173
00:06:26.690 --> 00:06:28.431
so Lance looks like the bad guy?

174
00:06:28.475 --> 00:06:30.259
Maybe.

175
00:06:31.695 --> 00:06:34.263
It might not be enough.

176
00:06:34.306 --> 00:06:36.700
You remember how the pastor used
the Christmas spirit

177
00:06:36.744 --> 00:06:38.528
to get you to meet Clara?

178
00:06:38.572 --> 00:06:39.660
Yeah.

179
00:06:39.703 --> 00:06:43.011
Well. juries are also
more inclined

180
00:06:43.054 --> 00:06:45.666
to be generous
around the holidays.

181
00:06:45.709 --> 00:06:47.450
Less likely to convict.

182
00:06:47.494 --> 00:06:49.931
Christmas is at the end
of next week.

183
00:06:49.974 --> 00:06:51.367
There's no way
we can squeeze this

184
00:06:51.411 --> 00:06:52.673
onto the docket before then.

185
00:06:52.716 --> 00:06:55.937
Chunk. my daughter got kidnapped
this year.

186
00:06:55.980 --> 00:06:57.460
We got her back.

187
00:06:57.504 --> 00:06:59.767
I got charged
with bribing a juror.

188
00:06:59.810 --> 00:07:01.159
We got me off.

189
00:07:01.203 --> 00:07:04.467
So. sue me if I'm feeling
a little bullish.

190
00:07:04.511 --> 00:07:06.513
♪

191
00:07:12.997 --> 00:07:14.172
Who says the holiday
season isn't filled

192
00:07:14.216 --> 00:07:15.609
with magic and wonder?

193
00:07:15.652 --> 00:07:18.133
You got Clara's case
on the docket?

194
00:07:18.176 --> 00:07:20.004
Dave from
the clerk's office gave us

195
00:07:20.048 --> 00:07:21.179
the last slot of the season.

196
00:07:21.223 --> 00:07:22.398
Told you helping him with

197
00:07:22.442 --> 00:07:23.878
those Friday crosswords
would pay off.

198
00:07:23.921 --> 00:07:26.881
I stand corrected and amazed.

199
00:07:26.924 --> 00:07:29.405
Now. I hate to be a downer...

200
00:07:29.449 --> 00:07:30.580
Then don't.

201
00:07:30.624 --> 00:07:32.060
Do you really think
that we can finish

202
00:07:32.103 --> 00:07:34.149
a manslaughter case
this fast?

203
00:07:34.192 --> 00:07:36.194
Speed is our friend here.
Round up the team.

204
00:07:36.238 --> 00:07:38.414
We need to move faster
than Santa's sleigh.

205
00:07:38.458 --> 00:07:41.243
You're really going all in on
the Christmas thing. aren't you?

206
00:07:41.286 --> 00:07:43.201
Oh. you know-ho-ho it.

207
00:07:44.768 --> 00:07:47.728
We are full speed ahead
on the Clara Williams case.

208
00:07:47.771 --> 00:07:49.164
Trial starts on Monday.

209
00:07:49.207 --> 00:07:50.992
Did you tell Bull that
come December 23

210
00:07:51.035 --> 00:07:52.907
I will be in Aruba.
no matter what?

211
00:07:52.950 --> 00:07:54.952
No. but I'm sure you will.

212
00:07:54.996 --> 00:07:57.085
We can work Christmas Day
for all I care.

213
00:07:57.128 --> 00:07:59.522
Erik took Mauricio
to Hawaii for the holidays

214
00:07:59.566 --> 00:08:01.437
so I'll be all
alone anyway.

215
00:08:01.481 --> 00:08:05.049
You said that so chipper
and yet it's actually sad.

216
00:08:05.093 --> 00:08:06.268
It is. a little.

217
00:08:06.311 --> 00:08:08.357
It's the first Christmas
without Mauricio

218
00:08:08.400 --> 00:08:10.751
since he was born.
but hey. no pity parties.

219
00:08:10.794 --> 00:08:14.494
I've got my Netflix cued up
and Hunan Delight on speed dial.

220
00:08:16.147 --> 00:08:18.236
What are you doing
for Christmas. Marissa?

221
00:08:18.280 --> 00:08:21.196
I am going to a dinner party
on Christmas Eve

222
00:08:21.239 --> 00:08:24.112
that I suspect is
a covert setup.

223
00:08:24.155 --> 00:08:25.722
My friend's brother
got divorced.

224
00:08:25.766 --> 00:08:27.637
and she keep dropping hints
about getting us together.

225
00:08:27.681 --> 00:08:28.899
That sounds awful.

226
00:08:28.943 --> 00:08:31.119
Why? Maybe he's amazing.
What's his deal?

227
00:08:31.162 --> 00:08:33.077
Well. he's handsome.
intriguing.

228
00:08:33.121 --> 00:08:35.819
and an archaeologist
of all things.

229
00:08:35.863 --> 00:08:37.604
Oh. I can dig that.

230
00:08:37.647 --> 00:08:39.170
Oh. Taylor.
No.

231
00:08:39.214 --> 00:08:41.433
Oh. you're all here.

232
00:08:41.477 --> 00:08:43.610
Thank you.

233
00:08:43.653 --> 00:08:45.263
So...

234
00:08:45.307 --> 00:08:47.701
In order for Clara to be
convicted of manslaughter.

235
00:08:47.744 --> 00:08:49.703
the A.D.A. has to prove that

236
00:08:49.746 --> 00:08:52.662
giving Dasha the fentanyl-laced
cocaine was reckless.

237
00:08:52.706 --> 00:08:54.534
But it was reckless.
I mean. if you ask me.

238
00:08:54.577 --> 00:08:56.361
Clara should've simply
refused to do it.

239
00:08:56.405 --> 00:08:59.669
Okay. well. remind me not
to put you on the witness list.

240
00:08:59.713 --> 00:09:02.280
We need to paint a picture
that it was impossible

241
00:09:02.324 --> 00:09:03.673
for Clara to say no;

242
00:09:03.717 --> 00:09:07.068
that she wasn't being reckless.
she was coerced.

243
00:09:07.111 --> 00:09:08.983
You're going after Clara's boss?

244
00:09:09.026 --> 00:09:11.855
Yep. Lance Thomas.

245
00:09:11.899 --> 00:09:13.248
Ranked the number one

246
00:09:13.291 --> 00:09:15.380
most powerful sports agent
by Forbes.

247
00:09:15.424 --> 00:09:17.426
And a notorious toxic bully.

248
00:09:17.469 --> 00:09:19.471
Between football and fashion.
I've seen this guy

249
00:09:19.515 --> 00:09:20.777
more times than I can count.

250
00:09:20.821 --> 00:09:22.474
He's only happy
when someone's crying.

251
00:09:22.518 --> 00:09:24.433
There are chatrooms devoted
to this guy.

252
00:09:24.476 --> 00:09:26.609
One user claiming to be
his ex-assistant said

253
00:09:26.653 --> 00:09:29.699
she got fired
for taking time off to do chemo.

254
00:09:29.743 --> 00:09:33.094
Another guy said
he had to sleep at the office

255
00:09:33.137 --> 00:09:34.356
because Lance threatened
to fire him

256
00:09:34.399 --> 00:09:36.140
if he ever beat
the kid into work.

257
00:09:36.184 --> 00:09:37.664
We need more
than Internet rumors.

258
00:09:37.707 --> 00:09:39.666
We need witnesses
that are willing to testify

259
00:09:39.709 --> 00:09:40.884
to his brutality.

260
00:09:40.928 --> 00:09:42.843
so it's not just
Clara's word against his.

261
00:09:42.886 --> 00:09:44.845
I'm on it.
Why aren't we going

262
00:09:44.888 --> 00:09:46.629
after Dasha Markovic's
responsibility?

263
00:09:46.673 --> 00:09:48.544
It's not like Clara
held her down

264
00:09:48.588 --> 00:09:50.024
and forced her
to snort that coke.

265
00:09:50.067 --> 00:09:52.069
Danny. you can testify
all day long.

266
00:09:52.113 --> 00:09:55.203
The woman is dead.
I would tread lightly there.

267
00:09:55.246 --> 00:09:56.683
Understood.

268
00:09:56.726 --> 00:09:57.684
Oh. and Danny...

269
00:09:57.727 --> 00:09:58.902
Yeah?

270
00:09:58.946 --> 00:10:00.251
I need you to track down
that drug dealer.

271
00:10:00.295 --> 00:10:01.644
See if you can get him
to testify

272
00:10:01.688 --> 00:10:04.038
that Lance sent all of
his assistants there

273
00:10:04.081 --> 00:10:05.822
to buy drugs for his clients.

274
00:10:05.866 --> 00:10:07.171
so we can establish the culture.

275
00:10:07.215 --> 00:10:09.347
Get a drug dealer
to rat on his customers

276
00:10:09.391 --> 00:10:11.567
and incriminate himself.
No problem.

277
00:10:11.611 --> 00:10:13.221
Anything else you want to ask
Santa for while he's at it?

278
00:10:13.264 --> 00:10:15.876
An acquittal. maybe.

279
00:10:20.707 --> 00:10:23.884
Yep. yeah. I just sent you
over a proposal.

280
00:10:23.927 --> 00:10:25.842
Take a look at it and
let me know what works for you.

281
00:10:25.886 --> 00:10:28.932
Yeah. Sounds good. Bye.

282
00:10:28.976 --> 00:10:30.325
Hey.

283
00:10:30.368 --> 00:10:32.153
Hey.
Ooh.
am I having a stroke.

284
00:10:32.196 --> 00:10:33.720
or is something burning?

285
00:10:33.763 --> 00:10:37.245
Ah! Damn it.

286
00:10:37.288 --> 00:10:39.639
Oh. shoot. Ah.

287
00:10:39.682 --> 00:10:42.337
Um. I got distracted
by my call.

288
00:10:43.643 --> 00:10:45.601
I guess December wasn't
the best time

289
00:10:45.645 --> 00:10:47.734
to start my consulting business.

290
00:10:47.777 --> 00:10:49.692
You know. I thought I'd have.
like. one client.

291
00:10:49.736 --> 00:10:51.694
All of a sudden.
I have seven businesses

292
00:10:51.738 --> 00:10:52.956
that want to redo
their brands.

293
00:10:53.000 --> 00:10:54.436
Yeah.

294
00:10:54.479 --> 00:10:56.917
Maybe you want to skip
the Christmas cookies this year.

295
00:10:56.960 --> 00:10:58.440
They're gingerbread men.

296
00:10:58.483 --> 00:11:00.660
And Astrid and I.
we were going to decorate them.

297
00:11:00.703 --> 00:11:02.487
and we were gonna put them
on the tree.

298
00:11:02.531 --> 00:11:04.054
Oh. the tree.
I just wanted to make

299
00:11:04.098 --> 00:11:05.882
Christmas really special
after the few months we've had.

300
00:11:05.926 --> 00:11:08.450
So. I just got off the phone
with the tree farm guy.

301
00:11:08.493 --> 00:11:09.669
It's kind of funny.

302
00:11:09.712 --> 00:11:12.715
He delivered the tree
to my old address.

303
00:11:12.759 --> 00:11:15.109
'cause I didn't update
the tree farm guy.
No.

304
00:11:15.152 --> 00:11:16.545
Oh. my-Can he bring us
another one?

305
00:11:16.588 --> 00:11:18.547
There's nothing available
till next week.

306
00:11:18.590 --> 00:11:20.244
No. No. no. That's too late.

307
00:11:20.288 --> 00:11:21.724
I'll figure out a time to go out...
No. no. no. no. No tree...

308
00:11:21.768 --> 00:11:23.508
But I have been
figuring it out.

309
00:11:23.552 --> 00:11:25.075
and I got this place.

310
00:11:25.119 --> 00:11:27.861
And they are gonna deliver
an eight-foot Douglas fir.

311
00:11:27.904 --> 00:11:29.253
extra plump.

312
00:11:29.297 --> 00:11:30.864
Ten-foot.

313
00:11:31.865 --> 00:11:33.083
She wants a ten-foot.

314
00:11:33.127 --> 00:11:35.651
There's the ten-foot
Douglas fir.

315
00:11:35.695 --> 00:11:36.957
Extra plumper.

316
00:11:42.832 --> 00:11:44.442
Izzy and I are going
all out this year.

317
00:11:44.486 --> 00:11:45.443
Ten-foot Douglas fir.

318
00:11:45.487 --> 00:11:46.662
fat as she comes.

319
00:11:46.706 --> 00:11:47.924
Let's hope we find
some jurors

320
00:11:47.968 --> 00:11:49.491
with as much Christmas
spirit as you.

321
00:11:49.534 --> 00:11:51.145
Mm-hmm. We want to
steer clear of rebels

322
00:11:51.188 --> 00:11:53.234
who would never cave
the way Clara did.

323
00:11:53.277 --> 00:11:56.498
What we want are conformists.

324
00:11:56.541 --> 00:11:58.021
If you're showing up
for jury duty.

325
00:11:58.065 --> 00:12:00.197
doesn't that kind of make you
a conformist already?

326
00:12:00.241 --> 00:12:01.851
That's true.

327
00:12:04.201 --> 00:12:05.942
Oh. God.
What?

328
00:12:05.986 --> 00:12:07.639
When I read that it was
A.D.A. Robert Jones.

329
00:12:07.683 --> 00:12:10.338
I didn't know that it was
that Robert Jones.

330
00:12:13.036 --> 00:12:15.386
Chester Palmer.

331
00:12:15.430 --> 00:12:16.779
Looks like we've got ourselves
a rematch.

332
00:12:16.823 --> 00:12:18.433
Rob. how are you?

333
00:12:18.476 --> 00:12:20.609
This is my colleague.
Dr. Jason Bull.

334
00:12:20.652 --> 00:12:22.437
Rob and I were
in law school together.

335
00:12:22.480 --> 00:12:23.525
Oh. I think it's fair to say

336
00:12:23.568 --> 00:12:25.788
I was Chunk's nemesis.
Hmm.

337
00:12:25.832 --> 00:12:27.398
That's funny.
He never mentioned you.

338
00:12:27.442 --> 00:12:29.836
Oh. well. nobody likes to relive
their defeats.

339
00:12:29.879 --> 00:12:32.795
Good luck. Rob.
You're gonna need it.

340
00:12:32.839 --> 00:12:34.405
Don't think so.

341
00:12:35.276 --> 00:12:38.192
Hmm. Chunk has
a nemesis.

342
00:12:38.235 --> 00:12:41.195
That guy. real gunner
in law school.

343
00:12:41.238 --> 00:12:42.370
Top of the class.

344
00:12:42.413 --> 00:12:44.024
Made law review.

345
00:12:44.067 --> 00:12:45.242
He and I made it to
the Moot Court

346
00:12:45.286 --> 00:12:47.331
competition finals.

347
00:12:48.115 --> 00:12:50.421
And?
He beat me.

348
00:12:50.465 --> 00:12:52.380
And he loved it.

349
00:12:52.423 --> 00:12:54.904
Well. let's flip the script
on that. shall we?

350
00:12:54.948 --> 00:12:56.732
♪

351
00:12:56.776 --> 00:12:57.907
Yeah.

352
00:12:57.951 --> 00:12:59.604
The first time
I drank alcohol was

353
00:12:59.648 --> 00:13:02.390
in high school at a graduation
party with my friends.

354
00:13:02.433 --> 00:13:04.000
And did you enjoy it?

355
00:13:04.044 --> 00:13:05.610
No.

356
00:13:05.654 --> 00:13:07.351
I spent the whole time worrying
about getting in trouble.

357
00:13:07.395 --> 00:13:08.613
I just wanted to fit in.

358
00:13:08.657 --> 00:13:09.876
Don't know what kind of person

359
00:13:09.919 --> 00:13:10.702
that makes me.

360
00:13:10.746 --> 00:13:12.487
It makes you a conformist.

361
00:13:12.530 --> 00:13:14.054
Hold up. Bull.

362
00:13:14.097 --> 00:13:16.404
Around the time juror
number nine had his first beer.

363
00:13:16.447 --> 00:13:18.536
he spearheaded
an environmental campaign

364
00:13:18.580 --> 00:13:20.887
when fish were washing up dead
in his hometown river.

365
00:13:20.930 --> 00:13:23.411
Does not sound
like conformity to me.

366
00:13:23.454 --> 00:13:24.586
Sounds like he's got a heart.

367
00:13:24.629 --> 00:13:26.327
You sure you're not going
too fast?

368
00:13:26.370 --> 00:13:27.763
If we don't seat a jury today.

369
00:13:27.807 --> 00:13:29.504
we will not finish the trial
by Christmas.

370
00:13:29.547 --> 00:13:30.897
If we don't finish the trial
by Christmas.

371
00:13:30.940 --> 00:13:33.813
we will miss out
on all that holiday cheer.

372
00:13:34.857 --> 00:13:36.250
So we go fast.

373
00:13:36.293 --> 00:13:38.252
This juror is acceptable
to the defense. Your Honor.

374
00:13:38.295 --> 00:13:41.037
Ten jurors sat in under an hour?

375
00:13:41.081 --> 00:13:43.257
I wish every lawyer
who came before me

376
00:13:43.300 --> 00:13:44.606
kept such an efficient pace.

377
00:13:44.649 --> 00:13:46.434
Uh. may I have
a moment to confer

378
00:13:46.477 --> 00:13:48.262
with defense counsel.
Your Honor?

379
00:13:48.305 --> 00:13:49.698
Make it quick. Counselor.

380
00:13:53.789 --> 00:13:56.574
Yeah. I'm starting to have
concerns about this jury pool.

381
00:13:56.618 --> 00:13:58.446
I'm thinking of moving
for a change of venue.

382
00:13:58.489 --> 00:14:00.274
That's ridiculous.
On what grounds?

383
00:14:00.317 --> 00:14:02.102
Oh. by the time I'm done
with my motion.

384
00:14:02.145 --> 00:14:03.407
I will have plenty of grounds.

385
00:14:03.451 --> 00:14:06.628
But I should let you know.
I write real slow.

386
00:14:06.671 --> 00:14:08.282
What do you want?A fair jury.

387
00:14:08.325 --> 00:14:09.457
Specifically.
Forty-four.

388
00:14:09.500 --> 00:14:11.372
No way. He's got obvious bias.

389
00:14:11.415 --> 00:14:12.939
His cousin OD'd.

390
00:14:12.982 --> 00:14:15.289
Yeah. Spent 25 years at
the same insurance company.

391
00:14:15.332 --> 00:14:17.682
Okay. 44. Are we done?
You bet. Oh.

392
00:14:17.726 --> 00:14:19.684
Oh. oh. wait. wait. wait.
Just one more thing.

393
00:14:19.728 --> 00:14:23.297
To feel 100% secure
in this venue.

394
00:14:23.340 --> 00:14:24.907
I will need juror number 26.

395
00:14:24.951 --> 00:14:29.042
Bull. juror number 26 is
a self-declared anarchist.

396
00:14:29.869 --> 00:14:31.653
Absolutely not.
Oh. well.

397
00:14:31.696 --> 00:14:33.046
then I'd better get started
on my motion.

398
00:14:33.089 --> 00:14:35.135
I hope you weren't planning
on taking advantage

399
00:14:35.178 --> 00:14:36.310
of the holiday spirit.

400
00:14:36.353 --> 00:14:37.833
Rob. you seem like
a very nice guy.

401
00:14:37.877 --> 00:14:39.487
so I'll be concise.
If you try to move my jury.

402
00:14:39.530 --> 00:14:42.316
I will file an extortion
complaint so fast

403
00:14:42.359 --> 00:14:43.839
it'll make your head spin.

404
00:14:45.188 --> 00:14:47.495
Your colleague came to play.
Mm.

405
00:14:47.538 --> 00:14:49.627
Juror 26 is a nonstarter.
Got it.

406
00:14:49.671 --> 00:14:53.196
Uh. will you accept
juror number seven?
Yes.

407
00:14:53.240 --> 00:14:54.589
Yes.
Yes.

408
00:14:54.632 --> 00:14:55.851
Well. we have a jury.

409
00:14:55.895 --> 00:14:57.679
Your Honor. uh.

410
00:14:57.722 --> 00:14:59.159
defense counsel and I
have agreed

411
00:14:59.202 --> 00:15:01.204
on jurors number 44

412
00:15:01.248 --> 00:15:02.945
and seven.

413
00:15:02.989 --> 00:15:04.294
Good.

414
00:15:04.338 --> 00:15:06.166
Opening arguments start
at 9:00 a.m. tomorrow.

415
00:15:06.209 --> 00:15:07.732
On the dot.

416
00:15:08.908 --> 00:15:10.518
That man gets
under my skin.

417
00:15:10.561 --> 00:15:11.954
Really? I hadn't noticed.

418
00:15:11.998 --> 00:15:13.608
We had better
win this thing.

419
00:15:13.651 --> 00:15:15.305
Well. the good thing about
fighting a peacock is.

420
00:15:15.349 --> 00:15:18.047
once you pluck all his feathers.
he's really just a tall chicken.

421
00:15:18.874 --> 00:15:21.007
How long you been
sitting on that?

422
00:15:21.050 --> 00:15:22.660
Couple hours.

423
00:15:29.406 --> 00:15:30.799
Getting cold out there.

424
00:15:30.842 --> 00:15:32.279
Might be a white Christmas.

425
00:15:32.322 --> 00:15:33.628
Or even a blizzard.

426
00:15:33.671 --> 00:15:35.369
They're predicting
quite a bit of snow.

427
00:15:35.412 --> 00:15:38.154
As long as it doesn't screw up
my flight to Aruba.

428
00:15:38.198 --> 00:15:39.547
Ooh.

429
00:15:39.590 --> 00:15:41.288
Opening arguments didn't go
so well. huh?

430
00:15:41.331 --> 00:15:42.811
Well. this A.D.A. isn't
playing around.

431
00:15:42.854 --> 00:15:44.204
He came in strong.

432
00:15:44.247 --> 00:15:45.901
But Chunk was able
to make up some ground.

433
00:15:45.945 --> 00:15:48.860
Where are we with Lance Thomas's
former assistants?

434
00:15:48.904 --> 00:15:51.211
Well. there's a woman he fired.
Melanie Standish.

435
00:15:51.254 --> 00:15:52.429
She works at a store
in Herald Square.

436
00:15:52.473 --> 00:15:53.909
She's willing to talk?

437
00:15:53.953 --> 00:15:55.563
Well. she'd rather not.

438
00:15:55.606 --> 00:15:57.043
but at least she didn't
hang up on me

439
00:15:57.086 --> 00:15:58.305
like all the other assistants.

440
00:15:58.348 --> 00:15:59.915
I've got until 5:00.

441
00:15:59.959 --> 00:16:01.612
I'll get her to talk.

442
00:16:03.440 --> 00:16:06.052
Miss Kiernan.
how did you know Dasha Markovic?

443
00:16:06.095 --> 00:16:09.751
We met on tour
when we were 16.

444
00:16:10.708 --> 00:16:13.407
It's a really
competitive atmosphere.

445
00:16:13.450 --> 00:16:15.496
so it can be hard
to make friends.

446
00:16:15.539 --> 00:16:19.326
But Dasha and I.
we just clicked.

447
00:16:19.369 --> 00:16:20.762
Sounds like you two were close.

448
00:16:20.805 --> 00:16:23.591
I got injured at
the French Open last year.

449
00:16:23.634 --> 00:16:25.941
I thought
my career was over.

450
00:16:25.985 --> 00:16:28.335
I was really depressed. and...

451
00:16:28.378 --> 00:16:29.945
I guess Dasha could tell.

452
00:16:29.989 --> 00:16:32.382
because one day I came home
after physical therapy.

453
00:16:32.426 --> 00:16:34.384
and... there she was.

454
00:16:34.428 --> 00:16:35.995
She flew all the way
to my hometown

455
00:16:36.038 --> 00:16:37.170
just to see me.

456
00:16:37.213 --> 00:16:39.607
I'm sorry. I just...

457
00:16:39.650 --> 00:16:41.435
I still can't believe
she's gone.

458
00:16:41.478 --> 00:16:45.134
I understand.
It's a... it's a huge loss.

459
00:16:46.440 --> 00:16:47.963
Thank you.

460
00:16:48.007 --> 00:16:49.530
Were you with Dasha

461
00:16:49.573 --> 00:16:51.184
the night before she died?

462
00:16:51.227 --> 00:16:53.012
I was.
And did someone

463
00:16:53.055 --> 00:16:56.624
bring her the fentanyl-laced
cocaine that night?

464
00:16:56.667 --> 00:16:58.191
Yes.

465
00:16:58.234 --> 00:16:59.235
Her.

466
00:16:59.279 --> 00:17:00.889
Clara Williams.

467
00:17:01.716 --> 00:17:04.197
I have no further questions.

468
00:17:07.113 --> 00:17:08.157
Miss Kiernan.

469
00:17:08.201 --> 00:17:09.637
did you ever see Dasha

470
00:17:09.680 --> 00:17:10.855
use cocaine?

471
00:17:10.899 --> 00:17:12.118
Yes.

472
00:17:12.161 --> 00:17:14.163
Shift the blame.
More than once?

473
00:17:14.207 --> 00:17:15.773
Yes.

474
00:17:15.817 --> 00:17:16.992
Objection. Your Honor.
Relevance?

475
00:17:17.036 --> 00:17:18.820
Dasha didn't die of

476
00:17:18.863 --> 00:17:20.474
a cocaine overdose.

477
00:17:20.517 --> 00:17:21.910
She died because the cocaine
Miss Williams supplied her with

478
00:17:21.953 --> 00:17:24.652
was laced with a fatal amount
of fentanyl.

479
00:17:24.695 --> 00:17:26.306
Shows a pattern of drug abuse.
Your Honor.

480
00:17:26.349 --> 00:17:29.091
Overruled. Proceed. Mr. Palmer.

481
00:17:29.135 --> 00:17:30.614
Would it be fair to say

482
00:17:30.658 --> 00:17:34.009
that you saw Dasha use cocaine
on many occasions?

483
00:17:34.053 --> 00:17:36.185
I guess so.

484
00:17:37.012 --> 00:17:38.274
One last question.

485
00:17:38.318 --> 00:17:40.276
On the night before
Dasha passed away.

486
00:17:40.320 --> 00:17:42.322
did you hear her call Clara

487
00:17:42.365 --> 00:17:44.498
and ask her to bring her
the cocaine?

488
00:17:50.069 --> 00:17:51.461
Yes.

489
00:17:51.505 --> 00:17:53.768
No further questions.

490
00:17:54.769 --> 00:17:57.206
Tell me you're seeing more
mistletoe than holly berries.

491
00:17:57.250 --> 00:18:01.297
I don't want to lie and end up
with a stocking full of coal.

492
00:18:01.341 --> 00:18:04.431
Jury doesn't want to blame
Dasha for her own death.

493
00:18:04.474 --> 00:18:07.260
We need to find a Scrooge
they can target.

494
00:18:07.303 --> 00:18:09.044
♪

495
00:18:09.088 --> 00:18:11.829
Sounds like Lance Thomas can be
a pretty tough boss.

496
00:18:11.873 --> 00:18:14.484
Told you. not gonna
talk about Lance.

497
00:18:14.528 --> 00:18:16.356
Well. he's not
your boss anymore.

498
00:18:16.399 --> 00:18:18.227
He can't get you fired.

499
00:18:18.271 --> 00:18:19.968
Well. wish someone could.

500
00:18:20.011 --> 00:18:22.057
Was Lance the reason
why you left the agency?

501
00:18:22.101 --> 00:18:25.060
Why you're stacking candles
two days before Christmas?

502
00:18:25.104 --> 00:18:26.366
Maybe.

503
00:18:26.409 --> 00:18:28.150
But I'm up for a job
at another agency.

504
00:18:28.194 --> 00:18:30.631
and I'm not about to blow it
by narcing on Lance.

505
00:18:30.674 --> 00:18:32.633
He knows everyone in sports.

506
00:18:32.676 --> 00:18:34.722
Well. sounds like Lance
could be pretty persuasive.

507
00:18:34.765 --> 00:18:37.028
Did he ever ask you
to buy drugs for a client?

508
00:18:37.072 --> 00:18:39.553
You do not give up. do you?

509
00:18:40.597 --> 00:18:43.557
Clara Williams is facing
15 years in prison

510
00:18:43.600 --> 00:18:45.950
because she did
what Lance told her to do.

511
00:18:45.994 --> 00:18:47.517
What if that had been you?

512
00:18:48.910 --> 00:18:50.172
Okay. look.

513
00:18:50.216 --> 00:18:52.087
You did not hear this from me.

514
00:18:52.131 --> 00:18:55.569
but check out
Crystal Meadows SoHo Rehab.

515
00:18:55.612 --> 00:18:56.831
Did he send clients there?

516
00:18:56.874 --> 00:18:59.660
Crystal Meadows SoHo.
Merry Christmas.

517
00:18:59.703 --> 00:19:02.271
And a happy new year.

518
00:19:04.099 --> 00:19:05.492
Mr. Thomas.

519
00:19:05.535 --> 00:19:07.407
what was your relationship
with Dasha Markovic?

520
00:19:07.450 --> 00:19:10.018
I was Dasha's agent.

521
00:19:10.061 --> 00:19:11.976
Signed her when she was just 13.

522
00:19:12.020 --> 00:19:14.762
She didn't make it to
the Junior Finals that year.

523
00:19:14.805 --> 00:19:17.025
but I could tell she was
gonna be one of the greats.

524
00:19:17.068 --> 00:19:20.115
I got her a new coach.
New trainer. Nutritionist.

525
00:19:20.159 --> 00:19:23.597
The next year.
she won the whole damn thing.

526
00:19:23.640 --> 00:19:26.165
and I got her
her first endorsement deal.

527
00:19:26.208 --> 00:19:28.602
Sounds like you made
quite the investment in Dasha.

528
00:19:28.645 --> 00:19:30.169
didn't you?Of course.

529
00:19:30.212 --> 00:19:32.214
It's what I do for my clients.
Whatever they need.

530
00:19:32.258 --> 00:19:34.260
Whatever they need. huh?

531
00:19:34.303 --> 00:19:35.913
Does that include
buying them drugs?

532
00:19:35.957 --> 00:19:38.307
No. of course not.
I would never do that.

533
00:19:38.351 --> 00:19:40.788
I-I'm sorry.
Not you personally.

534
00:19:40.831 --> 00:19:42.485
but you ask your assistants

535
00:19:42.529 --> 00:19:44.052
to buy them drugs.

536
00:19:44.095 --> 00:19:45.184
No. I do not ask

537
00:19:45.227 --> 00:19:47.098
my employees
to break the law.

538
00:19:47.142 --> 00:19:48.187
He's lying.

539
00:19:49.057 --> 00:19:50.798
Oh. I know.
Mr. Thomas.

540
00:19:50.841 --> 00:19:52.974
did you know that
Dasha abused cocaine?

541
00:19:53.017 --> 00:19:54.976
I was aware
that she used cocaine.

542
00:19:55.019 --> 00:19:57.457
but I did everything in
my power to discourage it.

543
00:19:57.500 --> 00:19:58.545
Did you know that

544
00:19:58.588 --> 00:20:00.547
she sought treatment last year

545
00:20:00.590 --> 00:20:03.114
at the Crystal Meadows
SoHo Rehab?

546
00:20:03.158 --> 00:20:05.160
Uh...

547
00:20:05.204 --> 00:20:07.293
I-I did know that she was there.

548
00:20:07.336 --> 00:20:11.122
and I was fully supportive
of her efforts to get clean.

549
00:20:11.166 --> 00:20:12.254
Well. if that's true.

550
00:20:12.298 --> 00:20:14.517
then why did you pull her out

551
00:20:14.561 --> 00:20:16.867
two weeks before she finished
her treatment?

552
00:20:17.781 --> 00:20:19.957
Dasha was the defending champ

553
00:20:20.001 --> 00:20:21.089
at the U.S. Open.

554
00:20:21.132 --> 00:20:22.743
She had worked her whole
life for this.

555
00:20:22.786 --> 00:20:24.962
and she wanted
to see it through.

556
00:20:25.006 --> 00:20:26.312
Whatever she needed.

557
00:20:26.355 --> 00:20:27.748
Right?
Dasha promised to go

558
00:20:27.791 --> 00:20:29.967
back to rehab
once the tourney was over.

559
00:20:30.011 --> 00:20:32.056
And did she go back
and complete her treatment?

560
00:20:32.100 --> 00:20:33.623
No. but the plan...

561
00:20:33.667 --> 00:20:36.800
In fact.
right after the tournament.

562
00:20:36.844 --> 00:20:39.977
she shot a commercial for which
you personally received

563
00:20:40.021 --> 00:20:42.153
$1 million.
isn't that right?

564
00:20:42.197 --> 00:20:44.591
That ad campaign had been
in the works for months.

565
00:20:44.634 --> 00:20:47.724
You removed her from rehab

566
00:20:47.768 --> 00:20:51.511
and now she's dead
from a drug overdose.

567
00:20:51.554 --> 00:20:53.513
♪

568
00:20:53.556 --> 00:20:55.906
Isn't that right?

569
00:21:00.389 --> 00:21:02.609
No further questions.
Your Honor.

570
00:21:09.442 --> 00:21:10.747
Mr. Thomas.

571
00:21:11.792 --> 00:21:14.838
Did you buy cocaine for Dasha
on the night she died?

572
00:21:14.882 --> 00:21:16.057
No.

573
00:21:16.100 --> 00:21:19.103
No further questions.
Your Honor.

574
00:21:20.104 --> 00:21:21.541
Guy's slippery as a snake.

575
00:21:21.584 --> 00:21:23.630
The witness or the A.D.A.?

576
00:21:24.413 --> 00:21:26.067
Counsel. please approach.

577
00:21:30.593 --> 00:21:32.160
As tomorrow is Christmas Eve.

578
00:21:32.203 --> 00:21:34.902
I'd like to reconvene
this trial after the holidays.

579
00:21:34.945 --> 00:21:38.253
Does the second week of January
work for both parties?

580
00:21:38.297 --> 00:21:39.733
Uh. no. Your Honor.

581
00:21:39.776 --> 00:21:42.126
my client has a right
to a swift and speedy trial.

582
00:21:42.170 --> 00:21:43.476
The courthouse is closed

583
00:21:43.519 --> 00:21:45.391
the first week of January.
Mr. Palmer.

584
00:21:45.434 --> 00:21:46.957
The second week is
what I can offer.

585
00:21:47.001 --> 00:21:48.568
But the courthouse is open
tomorrow.

586
00:21:48.611 --> 00:21:50.396
We can have this
wrapped up by then.

587
00:21:50.439 --> 00:21:52.180
I don't want to make
these jurors come in

588
00:21:52.223 --> 00:21:53.573
on Christmas Eve

589
00:21:53.616 --> 00:21:55.488
unless they're going to be
finished for good.

590
00:21:55.531 --> 00:21:57.620
We'll be finished.
Your Honor.

591
00:21:58.534 --> 00:22:00.710
A.D.A. Jones. any objections?

592
00:22:00.754 --> 00:22:02.930
No. No objections.
Your Honor.

593
00:22:02.973 --> 00:22:05.149
Okay then.
We'll wrap this up tomorrow.

594
00:22:05.193 --> 00:22:07.369
I'm sure the jury will be
pleased not to come back

595
00:22:07.413 --> 00:22:09.676
after the new year.

596
00:22:11.808 --> 00:22:13.810
Hey. do either of you know

597
00:22:13.854 --> 00:22:15.943
how to make
a raspberry cheesecake?

598
00:22:15.986 --> 00:22:17.597
God no. Why?

599
00:22:17.640 --> 00:22:19.599
Well. the archeologist
reached out.

600
00:22:19.642 --> 00:22:22.166
We've been texting.
He's funny.

601
00:22:22.210 --> 00:22:24.865
Curious how LOL leads
to cheesecake.

602
00:22:24.908 --> 00:22:27.128
I might have bragged that
I could make a mean one.

603
00:22:27.171 --> 00:22:29.783
Now I'm in charge of dessert
for tomorrow night.

604
00:22:29.826 --> 00:22:32.307
Ladies.
we're in a world of hurt.

605
00:22:32.351 --> 00:22:34.744
I need more ammunition
to throw the blame on Lance.

606
00:22:34.788 --> 00:22:36.006
Danny. did you track down

607
00:22:36.050 --> 00:22:37.486
the dealer Clara
bought the coke from?

608
00:22:37.530 --> 00:22:38.748
Yeah. I just found out
he got busted.

609
00:22:38.792 --> 00:22:40.533
and is being held at Rikers.

610
00:22:40.576 --> 00:22:42.099
Can you get in to see him today?

611
00:22:42.143 --> 00:22:44.406
I tried.
Uh. visiting hours are over.

612
00:22:44.450 --> 00:22:45.712
Can you see him tomorrow?

613
00:22:45.755 --> 00:22:47.888
I will be on the beach tomorrow.

614
00:22:49.237 --> 00:22:52.283
And Clara's going to be
in prison for 15 years

615
00:22:52.327 --> 00:22:54.503
if we don't dirty Lance up.

616
00:22:58.377 --> 00:23:00.335
Fine.

617
00:23:00.379 --> 00:23:02.032
I will change my flight.

618
00:23:02.076 --> 00:23:04.034
But I hate you.
You know that. right?

619
00:23:04.078 --> 00:23:06.036
Yes. Yes. I do.

620
00:23:06.080 --> 00:23:07.342
Good.

621
00:23:07.386 --> 00:23:10.214
♪ Oh. the weather outside
is frightful ♪

622
00:23:10.258 --> 00:23:13.435
♪ But the fire is
so delightful... ♪

623
00:23:13.479 --> 00:23:16.438
That snow is really
coming down out there.

624
00:23:16.482 --> 00:23:18.005
I'm telling you.

625
00:23:18.048 --> 00:23:20.703
And look at this. Fantastic.

626
00:23:20.747 --> 00:23:22.357
Okay. I'm gonna get changed.

627
00:23:22.401 --> 00:23:24.620
and then we are going
to decorate our tree.

628
00:23:24.664 --> 00:23:26.187
Oh. take your time.

629
00:23:26.230 --> 00:23:28.450
Where's the tree? I got an
email it arrived today.

630
00:23:28.494 --> 00:23:31.888
Oh. it arrived. Wait here.

631
00:23:31.932 --> 00:23:34.848
With all these cookies?

632
00:23:34.891 --> 00:23:36.502
Mmm.
♪ Let it snow. let it snow

633
00:23:36.545 --> 00:23:38.199
♪ Let it snow...

634
00:23:38.242 --> 00:23:39.809
Close your eyes.

635
00:23:39.853 --> 00:23:42.638
That's ominous.

636
00:23:45.380 --> 00:23:46.686
What the...?

637
00:23:48.252 --> 00:23:50.516
Oh.

638
00:23:50.559 --> 00:23:54.781
So. I ordered a ten-inch tree
instead of a ten-foot tree.

639
00:23:54.824 --> 00:23:56.826
Those pesky apostrophes.

640
00:23:56.870 --> 00:23:58.828
Well. so much for
a perfect Christmas.

641
00:23:58.872 --> 00:24:00.700
No. no. no. I promise you.

642
00:24:00.743 --> 00:24:02.963
I will get you
an adult-sized tree.

643
00:24:03.006 --> 00:24:05.487
♪ But as long
as you love me so ♪

644
00:24:05.531 --> 00:24:07.315
Mmm.

645
00:24:07.358 --> 00:24:09.491
♪ Let it snow.
let it snow. let it snow. ♪

646
00:24:12.146 --> 00:24:15.149
I'm starting to think that this
blizzard isn't gonna miss us.

647
00:24:15.192 --> 00:24:17.064
Ah. Such a

648
00:24:17.107 --> 00:24:18.935
beautiful tree.

649
00:24:18.979 --> 00:24:20.546
You know what else
will be beautiful?

650
00:24:20.589 --> 00:24:21.895
If Danny can get us
something useful

651
00:24:21.938 --> 00:24:23.723
from that drug dealer today.

652
00:24:23.766 --> 00:24:26.421
Good morning. Mr. Palmer.
Pastor Reynolds.

653
00:24:26.465 --> 00:24:29.511
I can't believe you came
all the way down to court today.

654
00:24:29.555 --> 00:24:31.165
I'm not a
fair-weather pastor.

655
00:24:31.208 --> 00:24:33.515
Hmm.
Am I gonna see you at
Midnight Mass tonight?

656
00:24:33.559 --> 00:24:35.648
Yeah. I'll be there.

657
00:24:35.691 --> 00:24:38.477
Do you go to church. Dr. Bull?

658
00:24:38.520 --> 00:24:42.176
Well. it's complicated.

659
00:24:42.219 --> 00:24:43.482
Is it?

660
00:24:43.525 --> 00:24:45.614
Okay. Pastor Reynolds.

661
00:24:45.658 --> 00:24:47.964
let's. uh...
let's go grab our seat.

662
00:24:51.794 --> 00:24:53.796
We've got a full day

663
00:24:53.840 --> 00:24:55.145
so let's get to it.

664
00:24:55.189 --> 00:24:56.277
Defense may call

665
00:24:56.320 --> 00:24:57.234
their first witness.

666
00:24:57.278 --> 00:24:58.671
The defense calls
Clara Williams

667
00:24:58.714 --> 00:25:00.063
to the stand.
Your Honor.

668
00:25:00.107 --> 00:25:01.935
Your Honor. before
Ms. Williams takes the stand.

669
00:25:01.978 --> 00:25:04.981
there's some evidence
I'd like to enter.

670
00:25:06.000 --> 00:25:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

671
00:25:14.817 --> 00:25:17.298
Your Honor. this
video is irrelevant

672
00:25:17.341 --> 00:25:19.866
to the events on the
night that Dasha died.

673
00:25:19.909 --> 00:25:21.302
We strongly object
to its inclusion.

674
00:25:21.345 --> 00:25:23.086
If the defendant is
going to take the stand

675
00:25:23.130 --> 00:25:25.175
and testify that she bought
drugs against her will.

676
00:25:25.219 --> 00:25:29.136
her personal history of drug use
is entirely relevant.

677
00:25:29.179 --> 00:25:31.138
I agree with A.D.A. Jones.

678
00:25:31.181 --> 00:25:32.618
I'll allow it.

679
00:25:32.661 --> 00:25:34.750
Your Honor.

680
00:25:34.794 --> 00:25:36.752
I-I need some
time to prepare.

681
00:25:36.796 --> 00:25:38.232
Defense assured the court

682
00:25:38.275 --> 00:25:39.799
they'd have proceedings
wrapped up by tonight.

683
00:25:39.842 --> 00:25:40.974
That's before counsel
sprung this video

684
00:25:41.017 --> 00:25:42.541
on us at the
last minute.

685
00:25:42.584 --> 00:25:45.935
I'll give you a brief recess
to prepare. Mr. Palmer.

686
00:25:53.943 --> 00:25:56.163
You should have shared
that video before trial.

687
00:25:56.206 --> 00:25:58.687
I am working well
within the lines.
That you keep redrawing.

688
00:25:58.731 --> 00:26:00.341
If you hadn't pushed
to finish trial today.

689
00:26:00.384 --> 00:26:02.996
you'd have plenty of time
to mitigate the fallout.

690
00:26:03.039 --> 00:26:05.346
That was always
your problem. Rob.

691
00:26:05.389 --> 00:26:07.957
You always got cocky
when you thought you were ahead.

692
00:26:08.001 --> 00:26:11.482
Chester... I am ahead.

693
00:26:18.141 --> 00:26:21.014
Oh. come on.
I'll give you an extra $200.

694
00:26:21.057 --> 00:26:23.190
What do you mean
you can't deliver it today?

695
00:26:23.233 --> 00:26:26.236
I'm not being a wise guy.

696
00:26:26.280 --> 00:26:27.890
Oh.

697
00:26:27.934 --> 00:26:30.589
Hey. Marissa.
do you have any connections

698
00:26:30.632 --> 00:26:32.155
in the Christmas tree business?

699
00:26:32.199 --> 00:26:33.853
Forget getting a tree.
You're not even gonna

700
00:26:33.896 --> 00:26:35.376
make it home
for Christmas Eve.

701
00:26:35.419 --> 00:26:36.812
What? Why not?

702
00:26:36.856 --> 00:26:38.422
Find a window.

703
00:26:40.337 --> 00:26:42.035
Oh.

704
00:26:42.078 --> 00:26:43.645
The blizzard just struck
New York City head-on.

705
00:26:43.689 --> 00:26:45.952
Roads are blocked.
Subways are down.

706
00:26:45.995 --> 00:26:47.954
We're snowed in.

707
00:26:47.997 --> 00:26:51.261
Ugh. There goes
my jury's Christmas spirit.

708
00:26:57.093 --> 00:26:58.573
I have some bad news.
Due to the blizzard.

709
00:26:58.617 --> 00:26:59.922
the mayor's office has issued

710
00:26:59.966 --> 00:27:02.316
an emergency declaration
restricting all

711
00:27:02.359 --> 00:27:03.752
non-essential travel.

712
00:27:03.796 --> 00:27:06.102
The roads. the subway.

713
00:27:06.146 --> 00:27:08.235
everything's shut down
until further notice.

714
00:27:08.278 --> 00:27:10.716
I apologize for the trouble

715
00:27:10.759 --> 00:27:12.674
that rushing this trial
has caused.

716
00:27:12.718 --> 00:27:17.287
but since there's nowhere we can
go. we might as well proceed.

717
00:27:17.331 --> 00:27:19.550
Clara. was that you who we saw

718
00:27:19.594 --> 00:27:22.031
using cocaine on that video?
Yes.

719
00:27:22.075 --> 00:27:23.685
Do you use cocaine regularly?

720
00:27:23.729 --> 00:27:27.384
No. That was the first and
only time I've ever tried it.

721
00:27:27.428 --> 00:27:30.213
Were you pressured
into using it?

722
00:27:30.257 --> 00:27:32.738
I was pressured
into doing a lot of things

723
00:27:32.781 --> 00:27:34.130
for my job. but not that.

724
00:27:34.174 --> 00:27:35.784
I wanted
to try cocaine that night.

725
00:27:35.828 --> 00:27:36.916
Why is that?

726
00:27:36.959 --> 00:27:38.004
I guess I just

727
00:27:38.047 --> 00:27:41.485
wanted to cut loose for once.

728
00:27:41.529 --> 00:27:44.227
Growing up. I didn't get
to go to a lot of parties.

729
00:27:44.271 --> 00:27:46.229
My family--
we didn't have a lot.

730
00:27:46.273 --> 00:27:48.231
I mean. my dad--
he worked really hard.

731
00:27:48.275 --> 00:27:50.233
but my mom passed away
when I was really young.

732
00:27:50.277 --> 00:27:55.282
so it was just him. raising five
kids on a bus driver's salary.

733
00:27:55.325 --> 00:27:58.111
And I had a job.
since I was 14. to help out.

734
00:27:58.154 --> 00:27:59.678
And I knew that if I wanted
to go to college.

735
00:27:59.721 --> 00:28:01.680
I was gonna have to work
way harder than everyone else.

736
00:28:01.723 --> 00:28:03.769
So I spent every moment I had

737
00:28:03.812 --> 00:28:05.988
studying or on the track.

738
00:28:06.032 --> 00:28:08.295
Anyway.

739
00:28:08.338 --> 00:28:10.776
that night. when I saw
everyone else doing it.

740
00:28:10.819 --> 00:28:12.603
I thought...

741
00:28:12.647 --> 00:28:15.389
maybe I could finally
have some fun. too.

742
00:28:15.432 --> 00:28:16.477
Was it fun?

743
00:28:16.520 --> 00:28:17.652
Not really.

744
00:28:17.696 --> 00:28:19.393
And now. seeing
what's happened to Dasha.

745
00:28:19.436 --> 00:28:21.264
I realize just how lucky I was
that there was no fentanyl

746
00:28:21.308 --> 00:28:22.701
in the cocaine I tried.

747
00:28:22.744 --> 00:28:25.834
Clara. why did you buy Dasha
that cocaine?

748
00:28:25.878 --> 00:28:27.531
I didn't feel like
I had a choice.

749
00:28:27.575 --> 00:28:30.056
I know that sounds crazy.
Of course I had a choice.

750
00:28:30.099 --> 00:28:32.058
But my boss. Lance Thomas--
he told me

751
00:28:32.101 --> 00:28:33.712
that he would fire me
if I didn't do it.

752
00:28:33.755 --> 00:28:36.715
And were you worried about how
you would support yourself

753
00:28:36.758 --> 00:28:38.325
if you lost your job?

754
00:28:38.368 --> 00:28:42.024
Well. I made minimum wage. and I
live in New York City. so. yeah.

755
00:28:43.112 --> 00:28:45.767
But it wasn't just
about the job for me.

756
00:28:45.811 --> 00:28:47.203
This was my dream.

757
00:28:47.247 --> 00:28:49.553
I wanted to represent athletes
more than anything.

758
00:28:49.597 --> 00:28:52.556
I wanted to be a voice for them.
I wanted to protect them.

759
00:28:52.600 --> 00:28:55.777
I didn't do everything
that I could to protect Dasha.

760
00:28:55.821 --> 00:28:59.041
I never should have gotten her
that cocaine.

761
00:28:59.085 --> 00:29:01.087
I'll regret the part I played
in Dasha's death

762
00:29:01.130 --> 00:29:03.393
for the rest of my life.

763
00:29:05.482 --> 00:29:08.703
No further questions.
Your Honor.

764
00:29:10.749 --> 00:29:12.968
Before Dasha's death.
were you aware

765
00:29:13.012 --> 00:29:15.754
that people could overdose
from drugs?

766
00:29:15.797 --> 00:29:17.494
Yes.

767
00:29:17.538 --> 00:29:21.324
And have you seen the-the signs
around town-subways. busses--

768
00:29:21.368 --> 00:29:24.066
that warn of the dangers
of fentanyl-laced drugs?

769
00:29:24.110 --> 00:29:26.068
I have.

770
00:29:26.112 --> 00:29:30.943
So is it fair to say
that you knew the risk.

771
00:29:30.986 --> 00:29:33.206
and yet.
you still supplied Dasha

772
00:29:33.249 --> 00:29:35.338
with the drugs that killed her?

773
00:29:37.776 --> 00:29:38.907
Yes.

774
00:29:38.951 --> 00:29:40.691
Nothing further.

775
00:29:42.563 --> 00:29:46.045
Well. I'm sorry. Bull.
The jury is as red as...

776
00:29:46.088 --> 00:29:48.699
I know I started it. but if you
use another Christmas metaphor.

777
00:29:48.743 --> 00:29:50.310
I'm gonna lose the will to live.

778
00:29:51.659 --> 00:29:54.401
That looks fabulous.

779
00:29:54.444 --> 00:29:56.403
Did you find a bakery?
Nope.

780
00:29:56.446 --> 00:29:58.927
Stayed up all night making it.
probably for nothing.

781
00:29:58.971 --> 00:30:00.494
Don't think I'll make it
to the party now.

782
00:30:00.537 --> 00:30:03.976
I'm sorry. At least
you're not snowed in at Rikers.

783
00:30:05.673 --> 00:30:08.110
Listen.
I came all the way out here.

784
00:30:08.154 --> 00:30:09.459
There's a freaking
blizzard outside.

785
00:30:09.503 --> 00:30:11.113
so I couldn't leave
even if I wanted to.

786
00:30:11.157 --> 00:30:12.811
Can you just let me speak
to him for a few minutes?

787
00:30:12.854 --> 00:30:15.814
You should have called ahead.
I would have told ya.

788
00:30:15.857 --> 00:30:18.294
No visitors are allowed
on Christmas Eve.

789
00:30:18.338 --> 00:30:19.730
Well. this isn't a social call.

790
00:30:19.774 --> 00:30:21.732
A young woman's life is
on the line.

791
00:30:21.776 --> 00:30:23.952
Would it kill you
to make an exception?

792
00:30:23.996 --> 00:30:26.128
No. But the paperwork might.

793
00:30:26.172 --> 00:30:28.130
Sorry. no can do.

794
00:30:29.740 --> 00:30:31.307
You see that suitcase
right there?

795
00:30:31.351 --> 00:30:33.179
I'm supposed to be
on a flight

796
00:30:33.222 --> 00:30:34.658
to Aruba right now.

797
00:30:34.702 --> 00:30:36.269
I was supposed
to actually leave last night.

798
00:30:36.312 --> 00:30:38.314
but I postponed my flight
to visit this inmate.

799
00:30:38.358 --> 00:30:40.316
And I get that none of
that is your problem.

800
00:30:40.360 --> 00:30:42.492
But I have had a rough
couple of months.

801
00:30:42.536 --> 00:30:44.886
My mom had a stroke.
and she and I...

802
00:30:44.930 --> 00:30:46.409
Well. it's never been easy.

803
00:30:46.453 --> 00:30:48.368
But I-I took leave from work
to take care of her.

804
00:30:48.411 --> 00:30:50.500
And when she recovered.
I said to myself.

805
00:30:50.544 --> 00:30:53.242
"Let's take care of me.
Let's-let's

806
00:30:53.286 --> 00:30:55.549
treat myself
to Christmas on the beach."

807
00:30:55.592 --> 00:30:59.118
But it seems like I'm gonna be.
uh. spending it here at Rikers.

808
00:30:59.161 --> 00:31:01.207
So if I'm gonna be stuck here.

809
00:31:01.250 --> 00:31:03.949
I would at least
like it to mean something.

810
00:31:03.992 --> 00:31:05.559
You done?

811
00:31:07.126 --> 00:31:09.519
Yes.

812
00:31:10.607 --> 00:31:13.262
My mom was a real piece
of work. too.

813
00:31:14.873 --> 00:31:17.571
Can you make it quick
before the shift change?

814
00:31:19.051 --> 00:31:21.488
Gone before you know it.
Thank you.

815
00:31:28.843 --> 00:31:30.236
Aha.
You heard from Danny?

816
00:31:30.279 --> 00:31:32.281
Not yet. Hey. you got any cash?

817
00:31:33.935 --> 00:31:35.719
You hungry?

818
00:31:35.763 --> 00:31:39.158
Yes. So's the jury.
The. uh...Oh.

819
00:31:39.201 --> 00:31:41.377
The cafeteria's closed
for the holiday.

820
00:31:41.421 --> 00:31:43.597
You can't sympathize
on an empty stomach. huh?

821
00:31:43.640 --> 00:31:46.208
No.
Least we can do is feed them.

822
00:31:46.252 --> 00:31:47.557
They're not gonna
make it home tonight.

823
00:31:47.601 --> 00:31:50.212
I don't think that
there's enough junk food

824
00:31:50.256 --> 00:31:52.214
in the world to turn
this jury around.

825
00:31:52.258 --> 00:31:56.392
I know. We need to stall.
give Danny enough time

826
00:31:56.436 --> 00:31:58.742
to figure some stuff out.

827
00:31:58.786 --> 00:32:01.441
I don't think Judge Tahani's
gonna do us any favors.

828
00:32:03.051 --> 00:32:04.835
Why don't you talk

829
00:32:04.879 --> 00:32:08.404
to your old pal Rob and see
if he'll take a plea deal?

830
00:32:08.448 --> 00:32:12.278
You-you want me to float
a plea deal as a stall tactic?

831
00:32:12.321 --> 00:32:15.324
Well. he would do the same
to us. wouldn't he?

832
00:32:16.978 --> 00:32:20.242
You summon me here to tell me
how the jurors ended up

833
00:32:20.286 --> 00:32:22.505
with a stocking
full of snacks?

834
00:32:22.549 --> 00:32:24.507
They don't know
who bought the snacks.

835
00:32:24.551 --> 00:32:26.727
For all they know.
you bought the trail mix

836
00:32:26.770 --> 00:32:28.207
and the cheese puffs.

837
00:32:28.250 --> 00:32:30.296
I was counting on the fact
that no one can sympathize

838
00:32:30.339 --> 00:32:32.080
on an empty stomach.

839
00:32:32.124 --> 00:32:34.430
Eh. Oh. well. I'm still winning.

840
00:32:34.474 --> 00:32:35.954
You don't stop. do you?

841
00:32:35.997 --> 00:32:37.956
Look. I know I come on strong.

842
00:32:37.999 --> 00:32:41.655
I've got a big personality. and
that's not to everyone's liking.

843
00:32:41.698 --> 00:32:44.963
But at my core.

844
00:32:45.006 --> 00:32:48.444
I'm just a kid from the sticks
looking to make good.

845
00:32:48.488 --> 00:32:50.272
You came from the sticks. huh?

846
00:32:50.316 --> 00:32:51.665
I grew up in a mobile home.

847
00:32:51.708 --> 00:32:54.146
I'm the first in my family
to go to college.

848
00:32:54.973 --> 00:32:56.322
I didn't know that.

849
00:32:56.365 --> 00:32:59.542
Yeah. well. clearly.
I overcompensate.

850
00:32:59.586 --> 00:33:02.110
So says my therapist.

851
00:33:02.154 --> 00:33:04.286
Don't quote me on this.

852
00:33:04.330 --> 00:33:07.333
but I can sympathize with Clara.

853
00:33:07.376 --> 00:33:10.640
I mean. when you come
from nothing.

854
00:33:10.684 --> 00:33:14.993
you will do anything
not to return to...

855
00:33:15.036 --> 00:33:16.820
nothing.

856
00:33:18.170 --> 00:33:20.476
I get that.

857
00:33:21.260 --> 00:33:23.697
Cheese puff?

858
00:33:23.740 --> 00:33:26.091
They're the perfect blend
of chemical and crunch.

859
00:33:30.356 --> 00:33:31.661
What are you doing?

860
00:33:31.705 --> 00:33:34.447
You have
a little something there.

861
00:33:35.274 --> 00:33:37.102
The playing
field's only fair

862
00:33:37.145 --> 00:33:39.713
when we both look our best.

863
00:33:40.583 --> 00:33:44.587
So I'm glad that you can
sympathize with Clara

864
00:33:44.631 --> 00:33:47.155
because I actually want to talk
about a plea deal.

865
00:33:47.199 --> 00:33:49.984
See what. if anything.
is on the table.

866
00:33:50.028 --> 00:33:51.768
A plea deal?Mm-hmm.

867
00:33:51.812 --> 00:33:55.511
Well. if you're serious. I'll
run it up the ladder to the D.A.

868
00:33:56.904 --> 00:33:58.993
I'd appreciate that.

869
00:34:01.735 --> 00:34:03.302
Hey. um...

870
00:34:04.477 --> 00:34:06.435
Would you ever be interested

871
00:34:06.479 --> 00:34:08.916
in catching up
over a drink sometime?

872
00:34:10.961 --> 00:34:14.704
I don't mean to imply
any quid pro quo with the plea.

873
00:34:14.748 --> 00:34:17.577
You know what?
Don't answer that

874
00:34:17.620 --> 00:34:20.362
until we're done
with all of this.

875
00:34:25.628 --> 00:34:29.023
As I predicted.
the dealer won't rat out Lance

876
00:34:29.067 --> 00:34:31.417
or his other customers.
What an upstanding guy.

877
00:34:31.460 --> 00:34:33.767
But he swears up and down there
was no fentanyl in his supply.

878
00:34:33.810 --> 00:34:35.203
I bet he does.

879
00:34:35.247 --> 00:34:36.596
Why did you make me
come here today?

880
00:34:36.639 --> 00:34:37.988
I don't have time for this.
Now I'm stuck here.

881
00:34:38.032 --> 00:34:40.556
Excuse me a moment. sir.
I may need you

882
00:34:40.600 --> 00:34:42.341
as a rebuttal witness.
I don't feel well.

883
00:34:42.384 --> 00:34:44.343
I need to get out of here
as soon as possible.

884
00:34:44.386 --> 00:34:46.388
I'm sorry. I'm on the phone.
Be right back.

885
00:34:46.432 --> 00:34:49.522
Hi. Sir. sorry about
that. So. listen.

886
00:34:54.353 --> 00:34:55.832
Bull? You there?

887
00:34:55.876 --> 00:34:57.225
Yeah.

888
00:34:57.269 --> 00:34:59.140
Well. the dealer claims
that he tests his stuff

889
00:34:59.184 --> 00:35:01.229
because dead customers
aren't return customers.

890
00:35:01.273 --> 00:35:04.406
Well. he's saying that so
he doesn't get prosecuted

891
00:35:04.450 --> 00:35:05.973
for Dasha's death.

892
00:35:06.016 --> 00:35:08.367
Maybe. but I had Taylor pull up
the arrest report.

893
00:35:08.410 --> 00:35:10.804
His house was raided the night
Clara bought drugs from him.

894
00:35:10.847 --> 00:35:14.199
and the coke the police
recovered had no fentanyl.

895
00:35:14.242 --> 00:35:17.463
So the fentanyl was added
after Clara bought it?

896
00:35:17.506 --> 00:35:19.421
Maybe Dasha juiced up
her own coke.

897
00:35:19.465 --> 00:35:21.423
Athletes can get hooked
on fentanyl patches.

898
00:35:21.467 --> 00:35:22.685
After they're injured.

899
00:35:22.729 --> 00:35:25.166
Did Dasha have an injury?

900
00:35:25.210 --> 00:35:26.950
I don't know.

901
00:35:26.994 --> 00:35:30.258
But there was someone else in
that room that night who did.

902
00:35:30.302 --> 00:35:34.828
Danny. you may have just
delivered a Christmas miracle.

903
00:35:40.138 --> 00:35:42.052
Are both parties ready
to give their closing arguments?

904
00:35:42.096 --> 00:35:43.750
Actually. Your Honor. we have
entered into plea negotiations.

905
00:35:43.793 --> 00:35:46.144
and the D.A. has authorized me
to make an offer.

906
00:35:46.187 --> 00:35:49.538
Your Honor. the defense is
no longer interested in a plea.

907
00:35:49.582 --> 00:35:51.758
You're not?
We'd like to enter into evidence

908
00:35:51.801 --> 00:35:53.194
this police report.
and we'd like

909
00:35:53.238 --> 00:35:55.240
to recall one
of the prosecution's witnesses.

910
00:35:55.283 --> 00:35:59.635
Ms. Kiernan. when you were
recovering from your hip injury.

911
00:35:59.679 --> 00:36:01.289
were you prescribed fentanyl?

912
00:36:01.333 --> 00:36:03.248
No. I don't think so.

913
00:36:03.291 --> 00:36:05.598
I would like to remind you
that you're under oath.

914
00:36:05.641 --> 00:36:07.121
I'd also like to inform you

915
00:36:07.165 --> 00:36:08.905
that all fentanyl prescriptions
are registered

916
00:36:08.949 --> 00:36:11.430
with the New York
Prescription Monitoring System.

917
00:36:11.473 --> 00:36:13.562
I wasn't able
to get access to the system.

918
00:36:13.606 --> 00:36:15.564
I'm not sure
Jade's in the database.

919
00:36:15.608 --> 00:36:18.524
Then it's a good thing
Jade doesn't know that.

920
00:36:18.567 --> 00:36:20.569
I was prescribed painkillers.

921
00:36:20.613 --> 00:36:22.658
I guess
they could've been fentanyl.

922
00:36:22.702 --> 00:36:24.660
And that's how you became
addicted to fentanyl?

923
00:36:24.704 --> 00:36:26.401
Objection. Speculation.

924
00:36:26.445 --> 00:36:29.099
I'll allow it.
Please answer the question.

925
00:36:29.143 --> 00:36:31.101
I'm not addicted to fentanyl.

926
00:36:34.192 --> 00:36:36.411
Feeling okay. Ms. Kiernan?

927
00:36:36.455 --> 00:36:39.109
I think I'm coming down
with something.

928
00:36:39.153 --> 00:36:41.286
Well. you seemed
okay yesterday.

929
00:36:41.329 --> 00:36:45.246
But you have been stuck in court
for quite some time.

930
00:36:45.290 --> 00:36:47.683
Mm. we all have.

931
00:36:47.727 --> 00:36:50.469
Did you know that fentanyl
withdrawal sets in

932
00:36:50.512 --> 00:36:52.427
after about eight hours.
roughly the amount of time

933
00:36:52.471 --> 00:36:53.994
that you've been here?

934
00:36:54.037 --> 00:36:55.038
Objection! Badgering.

935
00:36:55.082 --> 00:36:56.301
Sustained.

936
00:36:56.344 --> 00:36:57.606
Take it easy. Mr. Palmer.

937
00:36:57.650 --> 00:36:59.782
Bring it home
for the holidays. Chunk.

938
00:37:02.524 --> 00:37:04.134
Ms. Kiernan.

939
00:37:04.178 --> 00:37:06.224
are you aware the police raided
the home of the dealer

940
00:37:06.267 --> 00:37:10.097
who sold Clara the cocaine
shortly after she purchased it?

941
00:37:10.140 --> 00:37:11.229
No.

942
00:37:11.272 --> 00:37:12.795
Could you read for me

943
00:37:12.839 --> 00:37:14.928
the highlighted line
on this police report?

944
00:37:14.971 --> 00:37:18.148
"Field test fentanyl--
negative."

945
00:37:18.192 --> 00:37:20.325
I can't help wondering.

946
00:37:20.368 --> 00:37:23.893
If there was no fentanyl in the
cocaine that Clara purchased.

947
00:37:23.937 --> 00:37:27.288
how did it get into the cocaine
that Dasha ingested?

948
00:37:27.332 --> 00:37:28.637
I have no idea.

949
00:37:28.681 --> 00:37:30.291
You testified yesterday

950
00:37:30.335 --> 00:37:31.858
that you were with Dasha

951
00:37:31.901 --> 00:37:34.252
when Clara dropped off
the cocaine. isn't that right?

952
00:37:34.295 --> 00:37:35.644
Yes.

953
00:37:35.688 --> 00:37:37.342
Did you cut Dasha's cocaine
with fentanyl

954
00:37:37.385 --> 00:37:39.866
to get a better high?
Objection!

955
00:37:39.909 --> 00:37:41.694
This is gross speculation.
Overruled.

956
00:37:41.737 --> 00:37:43.696
Please answer the question.
Ms. Kiernan.

957
00:37:43.739 --> 00:37:46.394
No. I wouldn't do that.

958
00:37:46.438 --> 00:37:48.788
Dasha's dead because of you.
isn't she?

959
00:37:48.831 --> 00:37:50.311
Objection!

960
00:37:50.355 --> 00:37:53.053
Your Honor. this is outrageous.
I withdraw. Your Honor.

961
00:38:00.278 --> 00:38:04.369
Do you think that the jury
will believe Jade's responsible?

962
00:38:04.412 --> 00:38:06.109
I have no idea.

963
00:38:06.153 --> 00:38:08.198
Let us pray.

964
00:38:09.635 --> 00:38:12.551
Lord. we come to You
with humility.

965
00:38:12.594 --> 00:38:14.944
Have you reached a verdict?

966
00:38:14.988 --> 00:38:17.730
We have. Your Honor.

967
00:38:17.773 --> 00:38:19.819
On a night
in Bethlehem.

968
00:38:19.862 --> 00:38:23.518
with faith
as their only source of warmth.

969
00:38:23.562 --> 00:38:25.912
Your star as their guide...

970
00:38:25.955 --> 00:38:28.088
We. the jury. on the charge

971
00:38:28.131 --> 00:38:30.743
of misdemeanor possession
of a controlled substance.

972
00:38:30.786 --> 00:38:34.660
find the defendant.
Clara Williams. guilty.

973
00:38:36.444 --> 00:38:38.403
You sent them a son.

974
00:38:38.446 --> 00:38:41.623
and with that.
You gave us all redemption.

975
00:38:41.667 --> 00:38:44.452
On the charge
of negligent manslaughter...

976
00:38:45.801 --> 00:38:47.455
...we find the defendant

977
00:38:47.499 --> 00:38:49.588
not guilty.

978
00:38:49.631 --> 00:38:50.937
This trial is concluded.

979
00:38:50.980 --> 00:38:52.373
We thank the jury
for your service.

980
00:38:52.417 --> 00:38:54.767
Court is adjourned.

981
00:38:54.810 --> 00:38:58.031
Unto your Holiness. we say.

982
00:38:58.074 --> 00:38:59.424
amen.

983
00:38:59.467 --> 00:39:01.382
Amen.
Amen.

984
00:39:01.426 --> 00:39:03.776
The possession charge carries
about a year in prison.

985
00:39:03.819 --> 00:39:05.908
but we're gonna aim
for probation in sentencing.

986
00:39:05.952 --> 00:39:10.086
No matter what. it's better than
15 years in prison. Thank you.

987
00:39:12.698 --> 00:39:15.440
Looks like it let up.

988
00:39:15.483 --> 00:39:18.094
Yeah. Huh. No buses. but

989
00:39:18.138 --> 00:39:19.879
the subways are running.

990
00:39:19.922 --> 00:39:22.621
Nice job in there.
Thanks. You. too.

991
00:39:22.664 --> 00:39:25.754
Oh. Here comes your nemesis.

992
00:39:25.798 --> 00:39:28.714
I'm gonna jingle-jangle
on out of here.

993
00:39:28.757 --> 00:39:30.150
See you later.
Merry Christmas.

994
00:39:30.193 --> 00:39:31.238
Merry Christmas.

995
00:39:32.805 --> 00:39:34.807
Cheap tricks on
Christmas Eve?

996
00:39:34.850 --> 00:39:36.461
You ought to be
ashamed of yourself.

997
00:39:36.504 --> 00:39:38.245
I don't know what
you're talking about. Rob.

998
00:39:38.288 --> 00:39:40.900
You were just stalling for time
with that plea deal. Total BS.

999
00:39:40.943 --> 00:39:42.771
Are you mad because
you stuck your neck out

1000
00:39:42.815 --> 00:39:44.251
and asked the D.A.
for a plea deal?

1001
00:39:44.294 --> 00:39:46.558
Or are you mad because
you stuck your neck out

1002
00:39:46.601 --> 00:39:49.517
and asked me for a drink?

1003
00:39:49.561 --> 00:39:51.432
Little of both if
I'm being honest.

1004
00:39:51.476 --> 00:39:56.176
Well. if I'm being honest.
the answer was gonna be "yes."

1005
00:39:56.219 --> 00:39:58.570
I'll see you later. Rob.
Chester?

1006
00:39:59.788 --> 00:40:02.095
What about right now?

1007
00:40:04.358 --> 00:40:05.881
My party is
four blocks away.

1008
00:40:05.925 --> 00:40:08.493
I should be able
to walk that. right?
Totally.

1009
00:40:08.536 --> 00:40:10.495
Don't tell Bull but
I'm gonna sleep on his couch.

1010
00:40:10.538 --> 00:40:12.584
brave the snow
in the morning.

1011
00:40:12.627 --> 00:40:15.282
You sure you're gonna be
okay here? Alone?

1012
00:40:15.325 --> 00:40:19.286
Yes. I'll be fine. Go
meet your archeologist.

1013
00:40:20.069 --> 00:40:23.725
Hope he's a... real find.

1014
00:40:26.119 --> 00:40:28.382
♪

1015
00:40:46.139 --> 00:40:47.836
Still trying
to make it to Aruba?

1016
00:40:47.880 --> 00:40:50.709
At this point. I would just
settle for getting home.

1017
00:40:50.752 --> 00:40:53.102
Well. get in.
You're making that flight.

1018
00:40:53.146 --> 00:40:56.628
Let's roll!

1019
00:41:03.286 --> 00:41:05.288
I have two forks.

1020
00:41:05.332 --> 00:41:07.421
I'll share mine
if you share yours.

1021
00:41:07.465 --> 00:41:09.423
Snow too deep to walk?

1022
00:41:09.467 --> 00:41:12.165
Never made it outside.

1023
00:41:12.208 --> 00:41:15.385
Realized I'd rather spend
Christmas Eve with family

1024
00:41:15.429 --> 00:41:17.387
than some random guy.

1025
00:41:17.431 --> 00:41:19.999
Even an archeologist?

1026
00:41:20.042 --> 00:41:21.435
Just think of the dirt.

1027
00:41:21.479 --> 00:41:23.655
Here.

1028
00:41:23.698 --> 00:41:25.308
Thanks.

1029
00:41:25.352 --> 00:41:26.745
I hope it isn't
too sweet.

1030
00:41:26.788 --> 00:41:30.139
I meant thanks for...
coming back.

1031
00:41:30.183 --> 00:41:32.359
I know.

1032
00:41:35.928 --> 00:41:37.973
Ooh.Let's check this out.

1033
00:41:38.017 --> 00:41:40.323
Ah...

1034
00:41:43.762 --> 00:41:45.285
Ho. ho. ho!

1035
00:41:45.328 --> 00:41:47.983
You made it.
Why are you all wet?

1036
00:41:48.027 --> 00:41:49.985
Because I walked 40 blocks.

1037
00:41:50.029 --> 00:41:52.031
Aren't the subways back running?

1038
00:41:52.074 --> 00:41:55.817
You can't get one
of these on the subway.

1039
00:41:55.861 --> 00:41:59.299
♪ O Christmas tree...

1040
00:41:59.342 --> 00:42:00.561
That's...

1041
00:42:00.605 --> 00:42:04.173
The last tree on the lot.
no judgment.

1042
00:42:04.217 --> 00:42:08.047
I am not judging.
You got us a tree.

1043
00:42:08.090 --> 00:42:09.352
I know it's a little...

1044
00:42:09.396 --> 00:42:11.659
It's perfect.
Oh.

1045
00:42:11.703 --> 00:42:14.619
Merry Christmas.
Merry Christmas.

1046
00:42:14.662 --> 00:42:18.710
All right. let's
decorate this guy.

1047
00:42:19.928 --> 00:42:22.975
Astrid. Daddy got a tree.

1048
00:42:23.018 --> 00:42:25.281
♪ Your branches.

